      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOTTA HAV ME NZ (1) has come from wider or second row barriers in each of her three runs this campaign and was good when beaten only 3m here last week. That should have brought her to peak fitness and she is well served by the ace draw. AROMET GIRL (2) was a big improver second-up when she led from wider to score at Leeton, getting home by 2.5 metres. Likely to get the favours from this nice draw so could go on with it. LITTLE SASSY BOY (3) draws well and has claims of a win from the second line here two back. LIT THE WICK (6) has been about the mark of late and must be respected having worked from this barrier to finish 3.6m away last start.",
